## ğŸ” Authentication Flow

1. User logs in via `/login` â†’ Token stored in localStorage
2. Token automatically attached to all API requests via Axios interceptor
3. Auth state managed in Pinia store (`useAuthStore`)
4. Protected routes check authentication status via router guards
5. Unauthorized requests (401) automatically redirect to login

## ğŸ›£ï¸ Routing

- **Public routes**: Home, Quiz List, Quiz Detail, Leaderboard
- **Auth-only routes**: Dashboard, Quiz Take, Profile, Multiplayer
- **Role-based routes**: Quiz Create/Edit (teachers/admins), Admin Dashboard (admins only)

## ğŸ“¡ State Management

### Auth Store (`useAuthStore`)
```javascript
const authStore = useAuthStore()
authStore.login(credentials)
authStore.logout()
authStore.register(userData)
authStore.updateProfile(data)
```

### Quiz Store (`useQuizStore`)
```javascript
const quizStore = useQuizStore()
quizStore.fetchQuizzes()
quizStore.fetchQuizById(id)
quizStore.createQuiz(data)
quizStore.updateQuiz(id, data)
quizStore.deleteQuiz(id)
quizStore.submitQuiz(id, answers)
```

### Notification Store (`useNotificationStore`)
```javascript
const notificationStore = useNotificationStore()
notificationStore.success('Title', 'Message')
notificationStore.error('Title', 'Message')
notificationStore.warning('Title', 'Message')
notificationStore.info('Title', 'Message')
```

